<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>I have a frame with windows like this:</p> <pre><code>+---------------------+ | | | a | | | +---------------------+ | | | b | | | +---------------------+ </code></pre> <p>And I want this:</p> <pre><code>+---------+-----------+ | | | | a | | | | | +---------+ c | | | | | b | | | | | +---------+-----------+ </code></pre> <p>That is, I: - already have a top/bottom split, buffer a above b. - want to end up a right/left left split, where the left side is split in the same way as the original top/bottom split (buffer a above b). I don&#39;t mind having to switch buffers after splitting to get the right buffer at c.</p> <p>Is there a way to do that?</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/Jack-o-tall-tales"> /u/Jack-o-tall-tales </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/w7l3ls/is_there_a_way_to_split_the_whole_frame_vertically/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/w7l3ls/is_there_a_way_to_split_the_whole_frame_vertically/">[comments]</a></span>